metadata.title: De Havilland Canada Dash 8
aws::graph::propositions: De Havilland Canada Dash 8 Variants and Conversions
The French Sécurité Civile operate eight multi-role airtankers of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8.
Conair Group is currently operating a fleet of airtanker-only variants of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8 in Canada.
Conair Group is currently operating a fleet of airtanker-only variants of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8 in the US.
Conair Group is currently operating a fleet of airtanker-only variants of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8 in Australia.
Conair Group is currently operating a fleet of airtanker-only variants of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8 in France.
Conair manufactures the airtanker-only variant of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8 from their hangars in Abbotsford, Canada.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can carry 2642 US gallons of retardant.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can carry 2642 US gallons of foam.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can carry 2642 US gallons of water.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can carry 10,000 litres of retardant.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can carry 10,000 litres of foam.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can carry 10,000 litres of water.
The De Havilland Canada Dash 8 airtanker variant can travel at 340 knots (630 km/h).
DHC-8 MPA-D8 is a variant of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8.
DHC-8 MPA-D8 was converted in 2007 for use as a maritime patrol aircraft.
PAL Aerospace partnered to offer the DHC-8 MPA-D8 variant as DHC-8 MPA P4.
DHC-8-402PF is a variant of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8.
DHC-8-402PF is a converted pallet freighter variant with a payload of 9,000 kg (20,000 lb).
DHC-8-402PF was converted in 2008.
Q400CC is a variant of the De Havilland Canada Dash 8.
Q400CC is a cargo combi variant.
Q400CC seats 50 passengers plus 3,720 kg (8,200 lb) of payload.

text:
The French Sécurité Civile operate eight multi-role airtankers, while Conair Group is currently operating a fleet of airtanker-only variants in Canada, the US, Australia and France. Conair manufactures the airtanker-only variant from their hangars in  Abbotsford, Canada. This tanker can carry 2642 US gallons or 10,000 litres of retardant, foam or water and travel at 340 knots (630 km/h).
DHC-8 MPA-D8
2007 converted for use as a maritime patrol aircraft. PAL Aerospace partnered to offer this variant as DHC-8 MPA P4.
DHC-8-402PF
2008 converted pallet freighter variant with a payload of 9,000 kg (20,000 lb).
Q400CC
Cargo combi. Seats 50 passengers plus 3,720 kg (8,200 lb) of payload.
